It is proposed that stomp.py supports [MapMessage](https://activemq.apache.org/maven/apidocs/org/apache/activemq/command/ActiveMQMapMessage.html) and [ObjectMessage](https://activemq.apache.org/maven/apidocs/org/apache/activemq/command/ActiveMQObjectMessage.html) formats, which correspond naturally to Python `dict` and (pickleable) object structures.

This can be most easily achieved by specifying header `transformation=jms-map-json` and applying the following serialization/deserialization code:
````python
def to_map_json(obj):
    return json.dumps({'map':
                       {'entry':
                        [{'string': [str(key), str(value)]}
                         for key, value in obj.items()]}})

def from_map_json(body):
    print(body)
    return {i[0]: i[1]
            for item in json.loads(body)['map']['entry']
            for i in item.values()}
````

