Maybe rss/syndication is 'old school', but from what I've found when migrating and digging through the code, the syndication settings (synPropertiesForm) are currently not migrated from Archetypes to Dexterity in any version of p.a.contenttypes.

@pbauer as our 'migration pope', can you confirm that this is not in de code base yet or at least you haven't seen code for this so my assumption is correct that it's not there?

Shouldn't be too difficult (famous last words) to add this during the migration, it's probably copying the annotation if it exists, but I already checked it is non trivial to efficiently list syndicated folders in an existing site, there's no marker interface or similar to dig them up.

This xml attribute is missing in "Subscription.attributes", and requires an extension of __getpath__, like so :

```
def __getpath__(self, name):
    if name == 'plan_code':
        return 'plan/plan_code'
    elif name == 'plan_name':
        return 'plan/name'
    else:
        return name
```

Hi,
I noticed that in the latest Safari browser all fonts flicker when bootstrap3 carousel moves a slide. This affects only texts under the carousel.
To fix this problem I've added the following to my project:
```
.carousel-inner {
        -webkit-backface-visibility: hidden;
        -webkit-perspective: 1000;
}
```
I'm not sure if this is related directly to bootstrap-sass project. Can anyone clarify and apply the fix?

