Trying to debug a Javascript nbextension loading issue that worked in version 3.0, but not in 3.2.1.

I have code in IPython/html/templates/notebook.html that looks like:

```javascript
<script type="text/javascript">
    sys_info = {{sys_info}};
    require(['base/js/namespace', 'base/js/events'], function (IPython, events) {
	events.on("app_initialized.NotebookApp", function () {
            IPython.load_extensions("calico-publish",
                                    "calico-submit",
                                    "calico-spell-check",
                                    "calico-document-tools",
                                    "calico-cell-tools");
        });
    });
</script>
```
Some of those extensions have code that should run when the event `notebook_loaded.Notebook` fires. However, sometimes (about 50%) it appears that the extensions are loaded after that event has already fired, and so they don't do their tasks.

Here are a couple of pictures from the javascript console:

Example of the extensions being loaded late:

![screenshot from 2015-09-10 08 19 50](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/168568/9788085/b136e04a-5795-11e5-88ad-78555554a319.png)

Example of the extensions doing their tasks:

![screenshot from 2015-09-10 08 18 49](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/168568/9788089/b62be2d0-5795-11e5-9027-3a5067b8d742.png)

Am I loading the extensions in the wrong place (in the html template)? 

(About 5% of the time (depending on size of notebook it seems) the extensions don't load at all.)

Any suggestions/help appreciated!

